about.summary: Access services specified in OpenAPI (formerly Swagger) format. It is not a code generator. Client is generated dynamically as a list of R functions.

name: r-rapiclient
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '0.1.3' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-rapiclient
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/rapiclient_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/rapiclient/rapiclient_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: df6b9173e9a303e699187486455075788dfc50536035c8ea65e15ba15e9ba4de

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-yaml
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-httr
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-yaml

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('rapiclient')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('rapiclient')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/bergant/rapiclient
  license: MIT
  summary: Access services specified in OpenAPI (formerly Swagger) format. It is not a code generator.
    Client is generated dynamically as a list of R functions.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
